<Title>Features</Title>
</head>
<body bgcolor='#FFFFFF'>
<H1 align=CENTER>
<A HREF="http://gcrio.ciesin.org/educ/EarthSource.html">Earth Education Site</A> Features</H1>
<font size="+2><CENTER><b>Earth Education Site</b></CENTER></font>
<hr>

<blockquote><hr size="0.5" noshade>
<font size="+1">
The Earth Education Site <b>Features</b> is a monthly series of full-length articles. 
Through 
Features, we will seek out scientists on the cutting edge of research
about our 
Earth, follow trailblazing environmentalists, and check out
Earth-related education programs.  But most importantly, we will talk to
exceptional teachers from around the globe
and 
relay their knowledge and experiences to you!<p>

Our first feature articles focus on views from the classroom:<p>

<ul>
<li><b><A HREF="Tillery-Feature.html">Teacher, Weatherman, and Future Hurricane
Hunter:</A></b> An Interview
with Fairfax County's John Tillery, a
pioneering 
teacher in the use of direct readout reception from NOAA weather
satellites
to teach high school science.  In 1994 John was the first recipient of the 
Satellite Educator Award from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric 
Administration's (NOAA) National Environmental Satellite, Data, and
Information 
Service (NESDIS).<p>

<li><b><A HREF="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/papers/globeart.html">GLOBE Program
brings relevance to science 
activities for today's students</b></A>--this article originally appeared
in the
<i>Earth System Monitor</i> and provides some insights on how this major 
international education program is coordinating the work of students,
teachers, 
and scientists.<p>

</ul>
<font size="+2"><b>Let us know what feature articles you want to see in the 
future</b></font><p>


What do the frigid temperatures and crazy weather during the winter of 1996
have to 
do with global warming?  What are the expectations of faculty for college 
freshmen entering their environmental science programs?  What does an
Earth 
system scientist actually do?   Tell us what you want to learn about or
who you would like to 
hear from and we'll do the sleuthing!

<hr>
<CENTER><b>The Earth Education Site</b> -- A service of the Institute for Global
Environmental 
Strategies <IGES><p>

For more information about EarthRise, please contact:<p>

Theresa Schwerin<br>
Associate Director, Education<br>
Institute for Global Environmental Strategies<br>
1745 Jefferson Davis Highway<br>
Suite 306<br>
Arlington, Virginia 22202<br>
USA<br>
URL:  <A HREF="http://www.strategies.org">http://www.strategies.org</A><br>
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:theresa_schwerin@strategies.org">theresa_schwerin@strategies.org</A><p>

</CENTER>

