<html><head>
<title>GCRIO What Was Once New</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a>
<hr>

<h2>Previous GCRIO "What's New" Announcements</h2>

<h3>25 October 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt><img align=top src="/gifs/ball.yellow.gif">
<a href="EPA/sealevel/seatitle.html">The Probability of Sea Level Rise - An EPA
        Report</a>
        <dd>  Planning for sea level rise in response to changing climate
        depends on the probability that the sea will rise by a given magnitude.
        This report from the EPA develops probability-based projections that can
 be
        added to local tide-gauge trends to estimate future sea level at
        particular locations.<p></dl>

<h3>11 October 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt><img align=top src="/gifs/ball.yellow.gif">
<a href="CONSEQUENCES/introCON.html">
        CONSEQUENCES - The Nature & Implications of Environmental Change</a>
        <dd>The Summer 1995 issue of CONSEQUENCES (Vol 1, No 2) containing artic
les
        on "Global and U.S. National Population Trends", "Impacts of a
        Projected Depletion of the Ozone Layer", and "Potential Impacts of
        Climate Change on Agriculture and Food Supply" is now available.</dl><p>

<h3>6 October 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt><img align=top src="/gifs/ball.yellow.gif"><a href="USGCRP/LaJolla/cover.html">
        A Review of the U.S. Global Change Research Program and NASA's Mission
        to Planet Earth/Earth Observing System</a>
        <dd>Results of a National Research Council review of the U.S. Global
        Change Research Program with specific focus on the NASA Mission to
        Planet Earth (MTPE) and Earth Observing System (EOS) programs in
        light of budgetary pressures.  The <a href=USGCRP/LaJolla/Notice.html>
        print version</a> of the report is
        available from the National Research Council.
</dl>
<p>
<h3>20 September 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=newpubs.html>
        New Publication</a>
        <dd>The <a href=/ipcc/cover.html>Forum on Global Change Modeling</a>
	a brief statement on the credibility of projections of climate change
	provided by General Circulation Models (GCMs) as background for
	potential interpretation of model results in the context of
	developing and considering national policy options is now available
	from the GCRIO.</dl>
<h3>21 August 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=CSP/IR/title.html>
	U.S. Country Studies Program Interim Report on Climate Change Country
	Studies</a>
	<dd>Documents the significant achievements made by 21 of the 55
	countries that are conducting climate change country studies with 
	support from the U.S. Country Studies Program.  The reports discuss
	methods and results for inventories of sources and sinks of
	greenhouse gases, assessments of climate change vulnerability and
	adaptive responses, and evaluations of mitigation options to reduce
	net emissions of greenhouse gases.</dl><p>

<h3>17 August 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=GCDIS/iplan/tocgcdip.html>
	U.S. Global Change Data and Information System Implementation Plan</a>
	<dd>A report by the Committee on Environment and Natural Resources
	Research (CENR), the Global Change Data and Information System (GCDIS)
	Implementation Plan describes the coordinated effort being undertaken
	by participating federal agencies to implement the GCDIS.</dl><p>

<h3>3 August 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=fund.html>
	Inter-American Institute For Global Change Research Initial
	Science Program</a>
	<dd>A funding announcement from the Inter-American Institute for
	Global Change Research (IAI) Initial Science Program (ISP).  The
	IAI/ISP has as its purpose the support of science programs and
	activities in research, education and training, data and information
	management, communications, modeling, and/or other high priority areas.
	</dl><p>

<h3>3 August 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=gcacronyms.html>
	Global Change Acronyms and Abbreviations</a>
	<dd>Gathered from <a href=OCP/toc.html>Our Changing Planet</a> and 
	<a href=GCDIS/iplan/tocgcdip.html>
	The GCDIS Implementation Plan</a>, this list features over 200
	acronyms and abbreviations pertaining to the field of global change.
	The list can also be accessed from the <a href=oLnDoc.html>On-line
	Documents</a> section of our server.</dl><p>	

<h3>2 August 1995</h3>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=newpubs.html>
	New Publications</a>
	<dd>The GCRIO has two new publications available for distribution.  
	<a href=GCDIS/iplan/tocgcdip.html>The U.S. Global Change Data and 
	Information System 
	Implementation Plan</a>, a report by the
	Committee on Environment and Natural Resources Research, describes
	the actions being taken to implement the GCDIS.<br>
	<strong>The U.S. Interagency UV-Monitoring Network 
	Plan</strong>, written by the U.S. Global Change Research Program's
	Ultraviolet Radiation Panel, presents the first integrated national
	plan for UV monitoring.<p></dl>
	
<h3>28 June 1995</h3><p>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=USGCRP/seminar710.html>
	USGCRP 'Second Monday' Seminar Announcement</a>
	<dd>Announcing the latest USGCRP sponsored seminar to be held 10 July 
	1995 in Washington DC.<p></dl>

<h3>16 May 1995</h3><p>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=funds/woce.html>
	U.S. (WOCE) Program Announcements</a>
	<dd>U.S. World Ocean Circulation Experiment (WOCE) funding 
	announcement from the National Science Foundation.<p>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=funds/noaa.html>
	NOAA Climate and Global Change Program Announcement for FY
	1996</a>
	<dd>Global Change funding opportunities from the U.S. National 
	Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA).
</dl>

<h3>5 May 1995</h3><p>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=ipcc/cover.html>
	Forum on Global Change Modeling</a>
	<dd>Report of a forum arranged by the Subcommittee on Global Change
	Research assessing the state of current progress
	in improving understanding of global change and providing direction
	for future research.<p>
</dl>

<h3>28 April 1995</h3><p>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=gcact1990.html>
	The U.S. Global Change Research Program Act of 1990</a>
	<dd>Complete text of the law that establishes the USGCRP and GCRIO.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=edu.html>
	Education and Funding Resources</a>
	<dd>We've added several new links, including the Earth System Science 
	Community Curriculum Home Page and the Eisenhower National 
	Clearinghouse, in the Teaching Resources and
	Other Educational Resources sections of our server.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
	<a href=/USGCRP/ipccwg1.html>IPCC Working Group 1 draft Second 
	Assessment on Climate Change</a>
	<dd>An announcement that the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change 
	Working Group I 
	draft Second Assessment on Climate Change is available for comments.
</dl>

<h3>24 March 1995</h3><p>
<dl>
<dt>
<img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=IS.html>
	Bibliographic Database Systems</a>
        <dd>Searchable publication abstracts and titles.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=/CONSEQUENCES/introCON.html>
        CONSEQUENCES - The Nature & Implications of Environmental Change</a>
	<dd>A newsletter produced to provide reliable assessments of 
	practical concerns related to the consequences of changes in the
	global environment.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href="gopher://gopher.gcrio.org/11/GCRIO/holdings/">
        GCRIO Document Holdings</a>
        <dd>Search for information about global change publications available
        from the GCRIO.
</dl><p>
