<html>
<head>
<title>Bibliographic Data Bases</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<a name=#A> </a>
<p align=center>
<h1>Bibliographic Data Bases</h1>
<p align=left>
GCRIO provides access to bibliographic data bases that enable a user to 
identify relevant documents and publications based on free-text searches of the title, abstract, and various keywords.  GCRIO maintains its own bibliographic data base which consists primarily of information on global change-related documents that have been generated by US Federal Agencies and Organizations.  In parallel, some Agencies maintain their own bibliographic data base, and in an effort to minimize any duplication of effort, GCRIO simply provides links to those agency data bases.  Finally, GCRIO also provides links to other non-Federal and commercial bibliographic systems.  There are many such systems in the world today; we have tried to identify a few that contain information that is relevant to our mission area. (Many commercial services tend to be business oriented.)  Note that in most cases, one needs an account to use the commercial system.  This list is certainly not exhaustive.  We welcome suggestions for other relevant systems to add to our list. 
<p align=left>
<h2>Search/Browse the GCRIO Bibliographic Data Base</h2>
<ul>
<li>Freetext <a href="http://infoserver2.ciesin.org/Harvest/brokers/GCRIO-BibDb4/">search</a> of GCRIO Bibliographic Data Base</li>
<li>Browse GCRIO Bibliographic Data Base <B>(**Verbose)</B><a href=http://infoserver2.ciesin.org/Harvest/brokers/GCRIO-BibDb/difs.lst.html> with Author and Date</A></li>
<li>Browse GCRIO Bibliographic Data Base <B>(Concise)</B><A HREF=http://infoserver2.ciesin.org/Harvest/brokers/GCRIO-BibDb/difs.lst1.toc.html> Catalog</A></li>
</ul>
<EM>** WARNING: This file is 88K and growing, thus may take a moment to load.</EM>
<p>
<h2>Access US Federal Bibliographic Data Bases</h2>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.dtic.dla.mil/">Defense Technical Information Center</a>
<dd>Access to and transfer of scientific and technical information for DoD personnel, DoD contractors and potential contractors, and other U.S. Government agency personnel and their contractors.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.eren.doe.gov/">Energy Science and Technology Database (EDB)</a>
<dd>From the Department of Energy's Office of Science and Technical
Information (OSTI).
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.nalusda.gov/isis">USDA Integrated System for Information 
Services(ISIS)</a>
<dd>ISIS provides access to the National Agricultural Library's On-line 
Catalog and the the Journal Article Citation Database. This web page 
contains a telent link.  Users should login as ISIS.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://lcweb.loc.gov/homepage/online.html#locis">Library of Congress On-Line System (LOCIS)</a>
<dd>LOCIS is the Library of Congress's mainframe-based collection of data bases including a public access catalog of bibliographic information, federal legislation, copyrighted registered works, Braille and audio materials, organization and thematic guide

s, and foreign law abstracts.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.sti.nasa.gov/">NASA's Scientific and Technical Information Office</a> 
<dd>Access to the NASA RECON Bibliographic Database, NASA Thesaurus, and Selected Current Aerospace Notices.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.lib.noaa.gov/docs/e-pubs.htm">NOAA Digital Library</a>
<dd>A compendium of NOAA bibliographic data bases, on-line documents, and 
selected environmental journals.
 <p>
<dt><a href = "http://syssrv9.nrel.gov/documents/publications.html">National Renewable Energy Laboratory Publications Database</a> 
<dd>References to documents written or edited by staff and subcontractors of the National Renewable Energy Laboratory.
</dl>
<p>
<h2>Access Non-Federal and Commercial Bibliographic Data Bases</h2>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.biosis.org">BIOSIS</a>
<dd>From the Publisher of Biological Abstracts and Zoological Record
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.csa.com/csa-home.html">Cambridge Scientific Abstracts</a>
<dd>A detailed alphabetical listing of the extensive resources of Cambridge Scientific Abstracts
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://carl.org/carl.html">CARL</a>
<dd>Access to libraries and reference services from the Carl Corporation, A Knight Ridder Information Company
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://info.cas.org/welcome.html">Chemical Abstracts Service (CAS)</a>
<dd>A division of the American Chemical Society, CAS provides a broad range of scientific information products from focused technical publications to comprehensive on-line information resources.
<dd>
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.dialog.com">Dialog</a>
<dd>Access to the Knight-Ridder information systems including DIALOG, a 
service that provides access to over 450 on-line data bases and over 45 
CD-ROM titles, and UN_COVER, a self-serve periodical database with over 
17,000 periodicals listed.
<p align=left> <dt><a 
href="http://www.ei.org">Engineering Information</a>
<dd>Created to help engineers share their own research results and to learn about what other engineers are doing by facilitating access to the published engineering literature of the world.
<p align=left>
<dt> <a href="http://www.ns.doe.ca/cgi-bin/wais.pl">Environment Canada Database</a> 
<dd>A WAIS index to Environmental Information and Resources for Nova Scotia, 
New Brunswick, Prince Edward Island, and Newfoundland.  Includes listing of key publications.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://duke.usask.ca/~scottp/iii.html">Innovative Interfaces</a>
<dd>Web interface to libraries that use Innovative Interfaces software.  Libraries distributed worldwide.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.lexis-nexis.com/">Lexis/Nexis</a>
<dd>Products and services include Internet edition of the <i>NY Times</i>plus on-line search of news, business, financial, and legislative/political resources.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.questel.orbit.com/patents/patres.html">Questel/Orbit</a>
<dd>An international on-line information company specializing in patent, trademark, scientific, chemical, business and news information.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.silverplatter.com/">SilverPlatter</a>
<dd>Services include the Academic Reference Center, a bibliographic resources for the UK academic community.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.fiz-karlsruhe.de/stn.html">STN International</a>
<dd>The Scientific and Technical Information Network.  Provides access to many on-line data bases relating to science, technology, patents, and business.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.umi.com/""/>UMI</a>
<dd>Provides bibliographic, microfilming, and distribution services for doctoral dissertations and master's theses generated worldwide.  Also maintains an <i>Energy and Agriculture </i>research collection.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://wln.com/""/>WLN</a>
<dd>Products include a polar regions bibliographic data base.
</dl>
<p align=left>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href="/docpub.html">Documents and Publications</a>      |      <a href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
