<html>
<head>
<title>Catalog Systems</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<a name=#A> </a>
<p align=center>
<h1>Catalog Systems</h1>
<p align=left>
Catalog systems provide access to <strong>metadata</strong> or <i>information about data</i>.  Generally, these systems are used to identify, locate, and in some instances, browse, and order data and information resources of interest.  In general, there are two levels of "location metadata."  <strong>Directory-level metadata</strong> describes entire datasets or data resources at a very high level.  It tells a user about the existence and location of a dataset (i.e., what the content is, where it is archived, its temporal and spatial extent, and who to contact for more information.)  <strong>Inventory-level metadata</strong> describes individual products that are available from a particular dataset or data resource.
<p align=left>
<h2>US Federal Catalog Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://gcmd.gsfc.nasa.gov/">The Global Change Master Directory (GCMD)</a>
<dd>The GCMD provides access to directory-level metadata for global-change datasets and data resources that are developed, generated, and/or maintained by organizations and agencies involved in global environmental change research include those of the US Federal Government.  As such, the GCMD is one of the cornerstones of the GCDIS.  The GCMD is also one of the three coordinating nodes of the International Directory Network (IDN), sponsored by the Committee on Earth Observations Satellites (CEOS).
<p>
<dt><a href="http://ask.gcdis.usgcrp.gov:8080""/>The Global Change Assisted Search for Knowledge (GC-ASK)</a>
<dd>The Global Change Assisted Search for Knowledge (GC-ASK)  is the second of a series of incremental developments to provide the Global Change community with a comprehensive set of tools for accessing and exploiting diverse, distributed databases via the Internet. It builds upon the results of the "GCDIS Thesaurus Pilot Project, 1993," which provided a proof-of-concept for comprehensive searching of text databases. GC-ASK will provide a Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS)-based foundation for further development within and among Global Change participating agencies.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://www.esdim.noaa.gov/NOAA-Catalog""/NOAA-Catalog>The NOAA Data Set Catalog</a>
<dd>The NOAA Data Set Catalog is a forms-based tool that allows users to search directory-level metadata for publicly available environmental data held by public and private sources throughout the world.  Metadata are available for data in the following areas:  climatology, meteorology, ecology, pollution, geology, oceanography, and remote sensing.  The NOAA Data Set Catalog described the holdings of all three primary NOAA National Data Centers.  Specific dataset inventories for selected datasets can be accessed through the following home pages:  <a href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov">The National Climatic Data Center</a>, <a href="http://www.nodc.noaa.gov">The National Oceanographic Data Center</a>, and <a href="http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov">The National Geophysical Data Center</a>.
<p>
<dt><a href="gopher://esdim1.noaa.gov/7waissrc%3a/.wais_databases">National Environmental Data Referral Service (NEDRES)</a>
<dd>NEDRES contains directory-level metadata for over 22,000 environmental datasets from federal, state, private, public, and academic organizations.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/webglis">Global Land Information System (GLIS)</a>
<dd>The Global Land Information System (GLIS) is an on-line interactive computer system developed by the US Geological Survey for users seeking sources of information about the Earth's land surfaces.  GLIS contains directory-level and inventory-level metadata about datasets and their corresponding products and provides users the capability to browse samples of the data before placing an order on-line.
<p align=left>
<dt><a href="http://harp.gsfc.nasa.gov:1729/eosdis_documents">EOSDIS Version(0) Information Management System (IMS)</a>
<dd>The EOSDIS V0 Information Management System (IMS) provides access to directory-level, inventory-level, and guide information on datasets and their corresponding products that are archived at the various Distributed Active Archive Centers (DAACs) of EOSDIS.  Custom clients and a WWW interface are available.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.saa.noaa.gov/">NOAA Satellite Active Archive Inventory (WWW Interface)</a>
<dd>The Satellite Active Archive (SAA) Inventory contains a complete inventory of the Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR) level 1b datasets archived by NOAA.
<p>
</dl>
<h2>Non-Federal and Commercial Catalog Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/">The CIESIN Gateway (WWW interface)</a>
<dd>The CIESIN Gateway is a client-server data discovery tool that provides single point access to distributed set of heterogeneous directory and inventory servers distributed throughout the world.  Servers that can be accessed through Gateway include the Global Change Master Directory, the NOAA Directory, the EPA Directory, and the USDA Global Change Directory.  A user enters a query and the Gateway software distributes the query to each server in a form that it can understand, then collects and integrates the responses from each server and displays the search results in a common, standard format. Users can move transparently from directories to inventories and from either directories or inventories to html-based guides.  Users can <a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/">access documentation on Gateway or download a custom Gateway client </a> or use the WWW interface through the link listed above.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.grid.unep.no">UNEP GRID Metadata Data Base</a>
<dd>A web site that provides access to metadata describing the collections of data at various UNEP Global Resource Information Data Base (GRID) centers that distributed throughout the world.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.esrin.esa.it/">The European Space Agency (ESA) Prototype International Directory (PID)</a>
<dd>The ESA PID is one of  three coordinating nodes of the International Directory Network (IDN), sponsored by the Committee on Earth Observations Satellites (CEOS).
<p>
<dt><a href="telnet://NASDADIR@nsaeoc.eoc.nasda.go.jp/">The National Development Agency of Japan Directory (NASDADIR)</a>
<dd>The NASDADIR is one of  three coordinating nodes of the International Directory Network (IDN), sponsored by the Committee on Earth Observations Satellites (CEOS). This is a telnet link; users should login as <i>NASDADIR</i>.
<p>
<dt><a href="telnet://GCNET@gcnet.ccrs.emr.ca/">The Global Change Network (GCNet) (Canada)</a>
<dd>GCNet provide access to directory-level metadata for environmental datasets in Canada.  It is a cooperating node of the International Directory Network (IDN), sponsored by the Committee on Earth Observations Satellites (CEOS). This is a telnet link; users should login as <i>GCNET</i>.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.cms.udel.edu/index.html">Ocean Network Information Center (OCEANIC)</a>
<dd>OCEANIC provides inventory-level metadata for many products derived or generated as part of  both the World Ocean Circulation Experiment (WOCE) and the Tropical Ocean - Global Atmosphere (TOGA) Project
<p>
<dt><a href="telnet://zeno.gso.uri.edu">University of Rhode Island (URI) AVHRR Inventory</a>
<dd>URI maintains an inventory of Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR) datasets. This is a telnet link, plese login with user id uricat.
<p>
<dt><a href="telnet://FIFEUSER@plds3.gsfc.nasa.gov">First International Satellite Land Surface Climatology Project(ISLSCP) Field Experiment (FIFE)</a>
<dd>Inventory-level metadata for FIFE products can be obtained here.  This is a telnet link; users should login as <i>FIFEUSER</i>.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://gds.esrin.esa.it:80/80BF2923/CCS.SINFONIA">Earth Observation Satellite Data Inventory Service (SINFONIA)</a>
<dd>SINFONIA is an inventory system for data products derived from Landsat, SPOT, ERS, JERS, and MOS satellites.  It is operated and maintained by the European Space Agency.
</dl>
<p align=left>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href="/datainfo.html">Data and Information Resources</a>      |      <a href=#A>Topof This Page</a>      
