<html>
<head>
<title>Guide Systems</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<p align=center>
<h1>Guides</h1>
<p align=left>
Guide information is metadata whose function is to help a user utilize the data set rather than just identifying or locating it.  A data set guide can be thought of as a 
"User's Manual" that describes all aspects of the data set in great detail.  The concept of a "data set guide" has been expanded to include guides on satellites, sensors, programs, organizations, entire countries, and even issues or themes. 
<p align=left>
<h2>US Federal Guide Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://eos.nasa.gov/imswelcome">EOSDIS Version(0)
Information Management System (IMS)</a>
<dd>Directory-level, inventory-level, and guide information on data sets 
and their corresponding products that are archived at the various Distributed 
Active Archive Centers (DAACs) of EOSDIS.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://gcmd.gsfc.nasa.gov/">The Global Change Master Directory (GCMD)</a>
<dd>GCMD provides links from selected directory records to guide-like, detailed descriptions of satellites, sensors, campaign/projects, and data
 centers/archives. Users may also access these guide resources directly.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/webglis">Global Land Information System
</a>
<dd>The Global Land Information System (GLIS) is an interactive computer system
developed by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) for researchers seeking sources
of information about the Earth's land surfaces. GLIS contains metadata that is,
descriptive information about data sets. Through GLIS, researchers can evaluate
data sets, determine their availability, and place online requests for
products.
GLIS offers online samples of earth science data that may be ordered through
the system.
</dl>
<h2>Non-Federal and Commercial Guide Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/">The CIESIN Gateway (WWW interface)</a>
<dd>A client-server data discovery tool that provides single point access to a 
distributed set of heterogenous directory and inventory servers throughout the world.  Users can also move transparently from directories to inventories
 and from either directories or inventories to html-based guides.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/datasets/dataset-home.html">CIESIN Data Set Guides</a>
<dd>The descriptive information presented provides guidance in assessing the relevance and appropriateness of individual data resources, and assistance in their use.  Each data set guide includes an abstract describing the content and purpose of the data resource, information on existing documentation, availability of the data, access instructions, contact information,
 references to related data sets, as well as links to auxiliary information resources.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/IC/IC_partners.html">CIESIN Organizational Guides</a> <dd> Each Guide supplies the purpose, resources, location, and contacts for partner organizations in CIESIN's Information Cooperative. These
organizations
 are well-established data centers in government, non-government, and intergovernmental organizations.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/IC/IC_nodes.html">CIESIN Country Guides</a>
<dd>Country Guides offer a description of the countries that are partners in CIESIN's Information Cooperative.  A typical country guide provides access to social, economic, demographic, and geographical information about the country, its people and 
 customs.  Some country guides can be viewed both in English and the native language of that country.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/TG/thematic-home.html">CIESIN Thematic Guides</a> <dd>Overviews of key topics and issues pertaining to human interactions in global environmental change, these Guides combine hundreds of 
journal articles, book chapters, conference papers, government reports, and other materials to provide a current "snapshot" of the state of knowledge within that topic or issue. Thematic Guides also provide links to other relevant 
sources of information.<p>
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/kiosk/home.html">The CIESIN Kiosk</a>
<dd>An interactive electronic forum that facilitates sharing of information about global environmental change, the Kiosk includes unpublished scholarly papers and an electronic bookshelf that contains working papers or reports
published in less accessible publications.
<P>
</dl>
<p align=left>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a 
href=datainfo.html>Data and Information Resources</a>      |      <a 
href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
