<head>
<title>Data and Information  Systems</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<a name=#A> </a>
<p align=center>
<h1>Data and Information Systems</h1>
<p align=left>
Items on this page provide access to on-line data.  Most sites allow you to download data directly to your computer system. Metadata (information about the data such as observation methods and data quality) are often also available at these sites.  Some datasets have restrictions on their use.  For example, a dataset might not be quality-checked, and therefore not ready for analysis that would lead to publication.  It is important that you also view the metadata and "readme" files associated with a dataset or product.
<p>  
Some systems linked from this page let you order data from the host organization. Depending on the host, the data may be available on a number of media (printouts, floppy disks, tape, CD- ROMS, etc.).  Some datasets are free.  Others may be available for 
a nominal fee to cover the host organization's marginal cost of preparation, reproduction, and/or dissemination.
<p align=left>
<h2>US Federal Data and Information Systems</h2>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><h3>US Department of Energy</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://cdiac.esd.ornl.gov/cdiac">  Carbon Dioxide Information Analysis Center (CDIAC)</a> 
<dd>Trace gas emissions and atmospheric concentration, ocean chemistry, vegetation response, climate, land-use, ecosystems and coastal hazards.
<p>
</dl>
<p>

<dt><h3>US Department of Interior</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/webglis">  Global Land Information System</a> 
<dd>The Global Land Information System (GLIS) is an interactive computer system developed by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) for scientists seeking sources of information about the Earth's land surfaces. GLIS contains metadata that is, descriptive information about data sets. Through GLIS, scientists can evaluate data sets, determine their availability, and place online requests for products. GLIS is more than a mere list of products. It offers online samples of Earth science data that may be ordered through the system. 
<p>
<dt><a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/landdaac/1KM/1kmhomepage.html">Global 1 Km AVHRR Dataset</a>
<dd>The data set is composed of 5-channel, 10-bit, raw AVHRR data, at 
1.1-km resolution (at nadir) for every daily afternoon pass over all land 
and coastal zones using data from NOAA's polar-orbiting TIROS. Initially the data were to be collected 
continuously for 18 consecutive months beginning April 1, 1992, and 
continuing through September 30, 1993, subsequently the period has been extended to September 30, 1996. 
<p>
<dt><a href="http://164.159.188.82/">National Biological Survey InfoBase Server</a> 
<dd>A listing of all data and information resources availble through the NBS.  Many of the documents are indexed and available on-line.
<p>
</dl>
<p>
<dt><h3>Environmental Protection Agency</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.epa.gov/airs/airs.html">AIRS - Aerometric Information Retrieval System</a>
<dd>Computer-based inventory of airborne pollution for the US and for selected WHO member countries.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.epa.gov/tut/">TUT - Ozone Transport Assessment Group (OTAG) Emission Inventory Homepage</a>
<dd>TUT- The Ultimate Truth - the best data base representing 1990 emissions data for those states that particiapte in the Ozone Transport Assessment  Group.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.epa.gov/enviro/html/ef_home.html">Envirofacts</a>
<dd>Relational dat abase that integrates five major EPA Program systems:  AIRS/AFS, CERCLIS, PCS, RCRIS, and TRIS.  The data are updated monthly.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.epa.gov/epagiras.html">EPAGIRAS GIS Data Sets</a>
<dd>This is land use/ land cover digital data collected by USGS and converted to ARC/INFO by the EPA. This data is useful for environmental assessment of land use patterns with respect to water quality analysis, growth management, and other types of envir

onmental impact assessment. 
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.epa.gov/OSWRCRA/hazwaste/data">Hazardous Waste Data</a>
<dd>Collection of RCRIS and RCRA reports on hazardous waste.
</dl>
<p>
<dt><h3>National Aeronautics and Space Administration</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://harp.gsfc.nasa.gov:1729/eosdis_documents">EOSDIS Version 0 Information Management System (V0 IMS)</a>
<dd>"One stop shopping" for Earth science data archived in the multiple data centers of NASA's Earth Observing System Data and Information
 System (EOSDIS).
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.asf.alaska.edu">Alaska SAR Facility</a>
<dd>	Polar Processes, Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) products
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sun1.cr.usgs.gov/landdaac/landdaac.html">EROS Data Center</a>
<dd>Land Processes
<p>
<dt><a href="http://daac.gsfc.nasa.gov">Goddard Space Flight Center</a>
<dd>Upper atmosphere, global biosphere, atmospheric dynamics, geophysics
<p>
<dt><a href="http://podaac-www.jpl.nasa.gov">Jet Propulsion Laboratory</a>
<dd>Physical Oceanography
<p>
<dt><a href="http://eosdis.larc.nasa.gov">Langley Research Center</a>
<dd>Radiation budget, tropospheric chemistry, clouds, aerosols
<p>
<dt><a href="http://wwwdaac.msfc.nasa.gov">Marshall Space Flight Center</a>
<dd>Hydrologic cycle
<p>
<dt><a href="http://eosims.colorado.edu:1733">National Snow and Ice Data Center</a>
<dd>Snow and ice, cryosphere and climate
<p>
<dt><a href="http://cdiac.esd.ornl.gov/cdiac">  Carbon Dioxide Information Analysis Center (CDIAC)</a> 
<dd>Trace gas emissions and atmospheric concentration, ocean chemistry, vegetation response, climate, land-use, ecosystems and coastal hazards.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/">Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center</a>
<dd>Human interactions in global change
</dl>
<p>
<dt><h3>National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://radar.metr.uoknor.edu/pacrain/pacrain.htm"> Comprehensive Pacific Rainfall DataBase (CPRDB)</a> 
<dd>Daily rainfall observations from 1971 to the present for the  tropical western Pacific Ocean.
<p>
<dt>National Climatic Data Center
<dd><a href="http://hurricane.ncdc.noaa.gov/codiac/oasis-www.html">On-line Access and Service Information System 
(OASIS)</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/sdsd/oscar.html">On-line Satellite Catalog Request System (OSCAR)</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.saa.noaa.gov/"> Satellite Active Archive System (SAA)</a>
<p>
<dt>National Geophysical Data Center
 <dd><a href="http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/mgg/mggonline.html"> Marine Geology & Geophysics Databases </a>
 <dd><a href="http://nsidc.colorado.edu"> National Snow and Ice Data Center (NSIDC)</a>  
<dd><a href="http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/paleo/paleodat.html"> NOAA Paleoclimatology Program Data</a>
<p>
<dt>National Oceanographic Data Center
 <dd><a href="http://www.nodc.noaa.gov/GTSPP/gtspp-home.html"> Global Temperature-Salinity Pilot Project (GTSPP) 
Database</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.nodc.noaa.gov/NCAAS/ncaas-home.html">NOAA Coastwatch Archive and Access System (NCAAS)</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.soest.hawaii.edu/caldwell/index.html"> Shipboard Acoustic Doppler Current Profile Center 
(ADCP)</a> <p>
<dt><a href="http://www.cmdl.noaa.gov/ftpdata.html"> NOAA Climate Monitoring and Diagnostics Laboratory</a> 
<dd>Data from long-term measurements of important atmospheric trace gases, aerosols, and solar and terrestrial radiation.
<p>
</dl>
<dt><h3>National Science Foundation</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.ncar.ucar.edu/info/ResearchData.html"> National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Research Data Archives</a> 
<dd>Many atmospheric, oceanographic, and geophysical data sets and  metadata from the National Center for Atmospheric Research.
</dl>
</dl>
<p>
<p align=left>
<h2>Non-Federal and Commercial Data and Information Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/home-page/plue.page.html">Integrated Population, Land Use and Emissions</a>
<dd> SEDAC has linked georeferenced population data with gridded 1-kilometer seasonal land cover data from the EROS Data Center and developed interactive access services to make these integrated data available over the Internet. Selected data products for

 the U.S. are available now, including an archive of Census-related products.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/""> Consortium for International Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN) Gateway</a> <dd>A distributed information system for searching, viewing, browsing and ordering data on the human dimensions of global change  fro

m CIESIN.  Users can <a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/">access documentation on Gateway or download a custom Gateway client </a> or use the WWW interface through the link listed above.
<p>
</dl>
<p align=left>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href="/datainfo.html">Data and Information Resources</a>      |      <a href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
