<html>
<head>
<title>Browse and Visualization Systems</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<p align=center>
<h1>Browse and Visualization Systems</h1>
<p align=left>
Systems that enable the browsing or visualization of data are typically used to determine whether or not a particular product is suitable to a given application or requirement.  A browse entity often consists of a subset of the actual data product, and is intended to provide a representative sample of the content at reduced resolution. 
<p>  
There are two general browse methods.  In a static browse system, a user accesses browse products that have been pre-selected.  In a dynamic browse system, browse entities are generated "on the fly" in response to user requirements.
<p align=left>
<h2>US Federal Browse and Visualization Systems</h2>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><h3>Department of Interior</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/webglis">  Global Land Information System</a> 
<dd>The Global Land Information System (GLIS) is an interactive computer system
developed by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) for researchers seeking sources
of information about the Earth's land surfaces. GLIS contains metadata that is,
descriptive information about data sets. Through GLIS, researchers can evaluate
data sets, determine their availability, and place online requests for
products.
GLIS offers online samples of earth science data that may be ordered through
the system. 
<p>
</dl>
<p>
<dt><h3>National Aeronautics and Space Administration</h3>
<p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www-v0ims.gsfc.nasa.gov:1729/eosdis_documents/">EOSDIS Version 0 Information Management System (V0 IMS)</a>
<dd>"One stop shopping" for Earth science data archived in the multiple data centers of NASA's Earth Observing System Data and Information
 System (EOSDIS).
<p>
<dt><a href="http://seawifs.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEAWIFS/IMAGES/CZCS.html">SeaWiFS/CZCS Browse</a>
<dd>	Browse images of the Coastal Zone Color Scanner (CZCS) and SeaWiFS data from the SeaWiFS Project at the Goddard Space Flight Center (GSFC).
<p>
<dt><a href="http://rsd.gsfc.nasa.gov/rsd/images/">Image Catalog</a> at GSFC
<dd>A web page with many interesting environmentally-relevant browse images (hurricanes, forests, etc.)
<p>
<dt><a href="http://extreme.gsfc.nasa.gov/browse_samp.html">AVHRR Pathfinder</a>
<dd>Browse products from the Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR) Pathfinder Project at GSFC.
</dl>
</dl>
<p>
<p align=left>
<h2>Non-Federal and Commercial Data and Information Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/home-page/plue.page.html">CIESIN Integrated Population, Land Use and Emissions</a>
<dd> SEDAC has linked georeferenced population data with gridded 1-kilometer seasonal land cover data from the EROS Data Center and developed interactive access services to make these integrated data available over the Internet. Selected data products for the U.S. are available now, including an archive of Census-related products.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org/">CIESIN Gateway</a> <dd>A distributed information system for searching, viewing, browsing and ordering data on the human dimensions of global change from CIESIN.  Users can <a href="http://wwwgateway.ciesin.org">access documentation on Gateway</a> or use the WWW interface through the link listed above.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/plue/ddviewer/"> CIESIN Demographic Data Viewer</a> <dd>Generate maps of US Census Data down to the blockgroup level for any county, combination of counties, or state in the US.  
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/mva/">CIESIN Model Visualization and Analysis</a> 
<dd>Perform what-if and comparative analyses on the output of several different Integrated Assessment Models (IAMs).  Includes complete documentation on the models, their assumptions, and the various defined scenarios.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org//home-page/ulysses.guide.html">CIESIN Ulysses Census Cross-tabulation Engine</a> 
<dd>Interactively generate cross-tabulations from the Public Use Microdata Samples (PUMS) subsets of the US Census data for 1940-1990.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://sedac.ciesin.org/pidb/pidb-home.html"> CIESIN Policy Instruments Data Base</a> <dd>Data base of major environmental treaties and agreements.  Find important policy instruments by keyword or country and find out which countries are signatories.  Links to the full text of treaties and to treaty summaries are provided.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://www.cgd.ucar.edu:80/ccr/viz.html">GENESIS Earth System 
Modeling Project</a>
<dd>The scientific visualizations from the US National Center for Atmospheric
Research (NCAR) GENESIS project aid  in the analysis
of global climate research and communicate its findings through the creation of
broadcast quality video products.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://quasar.poly.edu:9090/WorldBank/sid.html"> World Bank Social Indicators of Development</a> 
<dd>A web interface into the World Bank's Social Indicators of Development (SID) data set.  Users select countries, years, and indicators of interest, and a table is created on the fly that presents the relevant data to the user.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://quasar.poly.edu:9090/WorldBank/tides.html"> World Bank Trends in Developing Economies</a> 
<dd>A web interface into the World Bank's Trends in Developing Economies (TIDE) data set.  Users select countries, years, and indicators of interest, and relevant text articles and selected and presented.
<p>
<dt><a href="http://shark1.esrin.esa.it">1km AVHRR Global Land Dataset </a> 
<dd>ESA/ESRIN Browse of the 1km AVHRR Global Land Dataset
</dl>
<p align=left>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href="/datainfo.html">Data and Information Resources</a>      |      <a href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
