<p align=center>
<h1>Participating Agencies and Organizations</h1>
<p align=left>
A number of Federal Agencies and Organizations participate in the USGCRP and GCDIS.  The exact number and composition changes slightly from year to year depending on a the respective agency or organization budget priorities.  The following list presents m
ore or less the active membership of the USGCRP.  
<p>
Each link below contains a brief summary of the agency's or organziation's contribution to the USGCRP plus a set of links to relevant web-based resources.
<ul>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/usda.html">Department of Agriculture</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/noaa.html">Department of Commerce/National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/dod.html">Department of Defense</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/doe.html">Department of Energy</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/hhs.html">Department Health and Human Services/National Institutes of Health</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/doi.html">Department of Interior</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/dos.html">Department of State</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/dot.html">Department of Transportation</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/epa.html">Environmental Protection Agency</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/nasa.html">National Aeronautics and Space Administration</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/nsf.html">National Science Foundation</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/si.html">Smithsonian Institution</a></li>
<li><a href="/USGCRP/tva.html">Tennessee Valley Authority</a></li>
</ul>
