<head>
<title>Electronic Mailing Lists for Global and Environmental Change Education</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<p align=center>
<h2>Electronic Mailing Lists for Global and Environmental Change Education</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.usra.edu/esse/ESSE.html">Earth System Science Education(ESSE)</a><br>
To encourage communication among ESSE program participants or those interested in the program.<p>
<li><a href="http://www.enviroindustry.com/">EON(Environment on the Net)</a><br>
Not for general environmental discussions, this list aims to specifically focus 
on techniques for effectively using the Internet and Intranets (including
Lotus Notes) for environmental applications from all sectors (academia, activist, government, and industry) and all perspectives. Further descriptive information provided along with information about a digest version.<p> 

<li><a href="http://www.vims.edu/adv/gc/gclist.html">Global Change Education Information List (gcei-l)</a><br>
Established to bring scientists and educators together to explore global  change issues 
and to discuss strategies for increasing public awareness.<p> 
<li><a href="http://www.sej.org/env_list.htm">Internet Mailing Lists on the 
Environment and Journalism</a><br>
Information about topical lists and includes Eco-curriculum, Ecology, Environment-L, and EnvJobs-l.<p>
<li><a href="http://www.liszt.com/">Liszt</a><br>
Perform a keyword search in this directory of e-mail groups to
retrieve a current list of mailing lists  with subscriber information, and for many, an in-depth description. The keywords, "science and education", produced almost 20 lists while "science and student" identified
more than 50 lists.<p>  
<li><a href="http://www.neosoft.com/internet/paml/bysubj.html">Publicly Accessible Mailing Lists</a><br>
Features a subject list with many environmental topics that includes Climate, Environment, Ecology, and Ecosystems.<p> 
<li><a href="http://science.cc.uwf.edu/">Science Education Associations Home Page</a><br>
Listserv functions to major associations that include: The National Association for Research in Science Teaching(NARST); The Association for the Education of Teachers in Science(AETS); and, The National Science Education Leadersip Association(NSELA).<p>
<p align=center>
<center>
<hr width=95% size=4>
<i>For comments, please contact the GCRIO Web Team at: <a href = "mailto:help@gcrio.org">help@gcrio.org</a>
</i>
<hr width=75% size=3></center> 
<center><i>Last updated 07/24/96</i></center>
