<html><head>
<title>GCRIO International Global Change Programs and Activities</title>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a>
<hr>
<h2>International Global Change Programs and Activities</h2><p>

In recent years the international scientific community has worked to
improve understanding of global environmental processes. Governmental,
intergovernmental, and nongovernmental organizations are developing
research programs and working groups to answer the fundamental question,
"How does the earth system work?" International global change programs
address scientific questions related to the global environment. Questions
put forth by these organizations and leading national programs have driven
much of the scientific research in this field. Many countries have
instituted national global change research programs.<p>

The international global change programs and activities include:<p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://kaos.erin.gov.au/erin.html">
	Australia's Environmental Resources Information Network (ERIN)</a>

<li><a href="http://datalib.library.ualberta.ca/cgcp/">
	Canadian Global Change Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.cisti.nrc.ca/programs/codata/welcome.html">
	Committee on Data for Science and Technology (CODATA)</a>

<li><a href="http://www.enrich.hi.is/">
	European Network for Research in Global Change (ENRICH)</a>

<li><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/TG/HDP/gergcr.html">
	German Global Change Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/docs/008-404/008-404.html">
	Global Change Programs in Finland and Switzerland</a>

<li><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/TG/HDP/hdp.html">
	Human Dimensions of Global Environmental Change Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.igbp.kva.se/">
	 International Geosphere-Biosphere Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.nies.go.jp">
	National Institute for Environmental Studies (NIES) - Japan</a>
 
<li><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/TG/HDP/netgcrp.html">
	Netherlands Global Change Research Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.rec.hu">
	 Regional Environmental Center for Central and Eastern Europe</a>

<li><a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/ukgeroff/welcome.htm">
	U.K. Global Environmental Change Office</a>

<li><a href="/unprogs/unprog.html">
	 United Nations Environment and Global Change Programs</a>

<li><a href="/CSP/webpage.html"> 
	U.S. Country Studies Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.usgcrp.gov">
	U.S. Global Change Research Program</a>

<li><a href="http://www.info.usaid.gov/">
	U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID)</a>

<li><a href="http://www.wmo.ch/web/wcrp/wcrp-home.html">
	World Climate Research Program</a>
</ul><p>
<center>
<hr width=95% size=4>
<i>For comments, please contact the GCRIO Web Team at: <a href = "mailto:help@gcrio.org">help@gcrio.org</a>
</i>
<hr width=75% size=3></center> 
<center><i>Last updated 10/22/96</i></center>
