<head>
<title>GCRIO Library Holdings</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a>
<hr>
<h2>Library Holdings </h2><p>

The GCRIO serves as a pointer to 
several libraries.  These may be smaller libraries that 
contain specialized information (such as the U. S. Environmental 
Protection Agency Library), or they may be general-purpose 
research libraries (such as the University of Michigan Library).  
Although the software for searching varies from system to system, 
the following library systems that can be connected to from the GCRIO 
allow searching of materials by author, title, subject, and keywords:<p>

<ul>
<li>	<a href=http://lcweb.loc.gov/homepage/>
	Library of Congress Home Page</a> 

<li><a href=gopher://poniecki.berkeley.edu:570>
	Central European Environmental Libraries Database</a> 

<li><a href=http://www-library.gsfc.nasa.gov>
	NASA Goddard Space Flight Center Library</a>

<li><a href=http://www.epa.gov/epahome/finding.html>
	U.S. Environmental Protection Agency Library</a> 

<li><a href=http://www.nalusda.gov>
	U.S. National Agricultural Library</a>

<li><a href=http://www.lib.noaa.gov/>
	U.S. NOAA Library Information Network (NOAALINC)</a> 

<li><a href=gopher://libgopher.yale.edu:70/11/>
	General Collection Libraries</a>
</ul>
<p>
<center>
<hr width=95% size=4>
<i>For comments, please contact the GCRIO Web Team at: <a href = "mailto:help@gc
rio.org">help@gcrio.org</a>
</i>
