<html>
<head>
<title>Bulletin Board Systems</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<a name=#A> </a>
<p align=center>
<h1>Bulletin Board Systems</h1>
<p align=left>
Bulletin Board Systems (BBSs) provide access to documents, data, 
software, and discussion groups covering a wide range of environmental 
topics.   Traditionally, BBSs were accessible via phone dial-up.  
Many of them are now accessible via the Internet.  Most BBSs ask a user for his/her name, address, and possibly other information when logging in.
<p align=left>
<h2>US Federal Bulletin Board Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<ul>
<li><a href="telnet://fedworld.gov">Fed World</a><br>
Fed World provides access to a large number of federally-maintained bulletin board services.  They are organized into subject categories; the Environment and Energy Mall seems particularly relevant.  This link connects (via telnet) to a FedWorld host,
 and a new is prompted for name, address, phone number, etc.  New users must define a password which is used for future accesses.  FedWorld also maintains a <a href="http://www.fedworld.gov/index.html"> web site</a>.
<p>
<li><a href="telnet://ttnbbs.rtpnc.epa.gov">EPA Technology Transfer Network Bulletin Board</a><br>
The EPA Technology Transfer Network Bulletin Board provides information on clear air admendments, air pollution, and emissions test methods.
<p>
<li><a href="telnet://gopher.c-wr.siu.edu:4503">WaterTalk</a><br>
The US Geological Survey sponsors WaterTalk, a bulletin board service that has discussions on hydrology, international water resources, groundwater quality, and water policy.
<p>
</ul>
<h2>Non-Federal and Commercial Bulletin Board Systems</h2>
<p align=left>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://dkeep.com/sbi.htm">Select BBSs on the Internet</a><br>
The web site is a listing of bulletin board systems that are accessible on the Internet.  It is maintained by Richard Marx and is the official BBS Internet list maintained by BBS Magazine.
</ul>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
<center>
<hr width=95% size=4>
<i>For comments, please contact the GCRIO Web Team at: <a href = "mailto:help@gcrio.org">help@gcrio.org</a>
</i>
<hr width=75% size=3></center> 
<center><i>Last updated 07/22/96</i></center>
</body>
</html>

