<head>
<title>GCRIO CD-ROM</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<h2>CD-ROM</h2>

Compact Disc Read-Only Memory (CD-ROMs) are convenient and inexpensive
media to store large amounts of data and information.  The information
stored on a CD-ROM may include data, text, graphics, audio, and software. 
Given the large amounts of information stored on a CD-ROM, and that many
data sets require more than one disc for storage, it is not practical to
access information from CD-ROMs on-line.  The following items
describe CD-ROM products that are available from
various sources.  Some of these products are free, but most are available
for a nominal processing fee.<p>

<ul>
<li><a href="/OnLnDat/cfr.html">
	Environmental Code of Federal Regulations CD-ROM</a>

<li><a href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/cdrom/cdrom.html">
	National Climatic Data Center CD-ROM (NCDC)</a>

<li><a href="http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov:80/newcd.html">
	National Geophysical Data Center CD-ROM (NGDC)</a>

<li><a href="http://www.nodc.noaa.gov/NODC-cdrom.html">
	National Oceanographic Data Center CD-ROM (NODC)</a>

<li><a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/cd-rom/cd-rom.html">
	NSSDC CD-ROM Catalog - May 1994</a>
</ul><p>
<center>
