<title>GCRIO Selected United Nations Documents</title>
</head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<a name=#A> </a>
<p align=center>
<h1>Selected United Nations Documents</h1>
<p align=left>
Links to selected environmental and global change-related documents from the United Nations are provided below.  
<p align=left>
<ul>
<li><a href="gopher://gopher.undp.org/11/unconfs/UNCED/English"> 1992 UNCED (Rio Summit) report</a><br>
A link to a gopher server that contains English versions of the UNCED Document collection.
<p>
<li><a href="/OnLnDoc/unepO3sum.html">Environmental Effects of Ozone Depletion
(Executive Summary)</a><br>
This United Nations Environmental Program (UNEP) report comes between the
Assessments of 1994
       and 1998 on the Environmental Effects of Ozone Depletion. The Executive
Summary presented here
       confirms previous research and presents new findings concerning: Ozone
and UV changes; health effects
       of ozone depletion; and the effects of ozone depletion on terrestrial and
aquatic ecosystems as well as on
       biogeochemical cycles and air quality.
<p>

<li><a href="/OnLnDoc/oslo.html"> Oslo Roundtable Conference on Sustainable Production and Consumption</a><br>
A statement by Elizabeth Dowdeswell, Executive Director of the UNEP, at the Oslo Roundtable Conference on Sustainable Production and Consumption (8 Feb 1995).
<p>
<li><a href="http://www.undp.org/un/un_confs.html">UN Conference Documents</a><br>
A web page maintained by UNDP that lists upcoming UN Summits and Conferences.
<p>
<li><a href="http://www.undp.org/un/un_docs.html">UN General Assembly Documents</a><br>
A web page maintained by UNDP that contains General Assembly Documents, Secretary General Reports, Security Council Resolutions, and Economic and Social Council Resolutions.
<p>
<li><a href="gopher://gopher.undp.org:70/11/uncurr/press_releases">UN Press Releases</a><br>
A gopher server maintained by UNDP that lists current UN press releases.
</ul>
<p>
