<html>
<TITLE>Welcome to the Earth Education Site!</TITLE>
<body bgcolor='#FFFFFF'>
<hr size=4>
<Center><h1>Welcome to the <A HREF="http://gcrio.ciesin.org/educ/EarthSource.html
">Earth Education Site</A></h1></Center>
<hr size=4>
<p>
The Earth Education Site is a unique, Internet-based communication system for Ea
rth-focused education information, including:<p>
<ul>
<li><b>Interactions of the Earth System </b><br>
oceans, continents, snow cover and sea ice, atmosphere, and life<p>
<li><b>Global Environmental Changes</b><br>
the impact of changes on climate, surface UV radiation, land cover, the health o
f terrestrial and marine ecosystems, and the availability of future resources<p>
<li><b>Education for Sustainability</b><br>
including the three "e"s: environmental education, economics, and equity<p>
<li><b>Environmental Technology</b><br>
satellite remote sensing, geographic information systems, etc.
</ul><p>
The Earth Education Site is designed to help teachers and students; program plan
ners, managers, and administrators; policy makers; and museum and library person
nel to locate and obtain information on current and planned Earth-related topics
 and activities, including:<p>
<ul>
<li>Searchable databases of programs, resources, and events that will enable you
 to retrieve important information within seconds;<p>
<li>a newsletter posting short, timely, and relevant new items;<p>
<li>a series of multi-media feature articles on exciting topics;<p>
<li>an interactive conference series with national science and education experts
;<p>
<li>an teamwork capability that can enable you to communicate with your colleagu
es around the world or to work on focused research projects
</ul>
<p>
The Earth Education Site is currently under development by the Institute for Glo
bal Environmental Strategies <A HREF="http://www.strategies.org">(IGES)</A> and
the Consortium for International Earth Science Information Network <A HREF="http
://www.ciesin.org/"> (CIESIN)</A>, through initial funding from IGES, the Nation
al Aeronautics and Space Administration's (NASA) Office of Mission to Planet Ear
th <A HREF=" http://mercury.hq.nasa.gov/office/mtpe/">(MTPE)</A>, and the Nation
al Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's <A HREF="http://www.noaa.gov">(NOAA)
</A> National Environmental Satellite, Data, and Information Service <A HREF=" h
ttp://www.noaa.gov/nesdis/nesdis_intro.html">(NESDIS)</A>.
<p>
