<html><head><title>CENR PROGRAM GUIDE - OPPORTUNITIES BY 
AGENCY
 </title></head>
<body>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-
header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>

<p>
<center><H2>OPPORTUNITIES BY AGENCY
</H2></center><P>This section describes the types of environment and 
natural 
resources
R&amp;D  currently supported by Federal agencies, potential opportunities
for funding,  and points of contact. This <i>Program Guide</i> is meant to 
provide
the reader  with an understanding of the scope of federally funded 
environment
and  natural resources research opportunities. While every effort was made
to  ensure completeness in the programs described here, there may be 
additional
 programs that are not included. The CENR intends to update this 
<i>Guide</i> 
routinely, and add any programs that have been omitted.
<P>For additional or more detailed information on the programs described
 below, the reader should communicate with the point of contact listed. 
 Further, agencies are required to advertise their research opportunities
prior  to issuing a solicitation in the <i>Commerce Business Daily,   </i> 
which is
available  electronically. Some agencies, such as NASA, advertise 
solicitations
via the  Internet. These on-line sources can be accessed through the
White House Home Page <A 
HREF="http://www.whitehouse.gov">(http://www.whitehouse.gov)</A>.
<P>Although many of the deadlines for submitting FY96 proposals have 
passed,
 they have been left here for informational purposes. Many of the research
 areas noted for 1996 will continue in 1997.

<p>

<center>
<hr width=95% size=4>
<i>For comments, please contact the GCRIO Web Team at: <a href = 
"mailto:help@gcrio.org">help@gcrio.org</a>
</i>
</center> 

</body></html>

</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT12-B36-69</DOCNO>
