<LI><i>Natural Hazard Reduction</i> researches the causes and effects
of
natural
 hazards, societal and behavioral responses, and the means for reducing their
 impacts, including weather-related hazards (storms, hurricanes, typhoons,
 tornadoes, floods, droughts), geological hazards (volcanoes, earthquakes),
and  wildfires. NSF is a participant in the interagency U.S. Weather Research
 Program, the National Space Weather Program, and the National Earthquake
 Hazards Reduction Program (NEHRP).<BR> 
	<STRONG>Contacts:</STRONG> <BR>Eleonora
