Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory (LLNL), Livermore, CA.

<li>Dickinson, R.E., 1985:  Modeling evapotranspiration for three-
dimensional global climate models.  In <em>Climate Processes and 
Climate Sensitivity</em>, J.E. Hansen and T. Takahashi, eds., Maurice 
Ewing Series, Vol. 5, American Geophysical Union, Washington DC, pp. 
58-72.

<li>Bradley, R.S. and P.D. Jones, 1993:  The "Little Ice Age" summer 
temperature variations:  Their nature and relevance to global 
warming trends, <em>The Holocene,</em> 3, pp. 367-376.

<li>Oxygen isotope record data:  P.M. Grootes and M. Stuiver, 
University of Washington; and Greenland Ice Sheet Project 2 (GISP2), 
University of New Hampshire.  [See also Grootes, P.M., M. Stuiver, 
J.W.C. White, S. Johnsen, and J. Jouzel, 1993:  Comparison of oxygen 
isotope records from the GISP2 and GRIP Greenland ice cores, 
<em>Nature,</em> 366, pp. 552-554.].</ol><p>

<a href=partagency.html><img align=middle alt=To next section 
src=gifs/forward.gif> Go to Participating Agencies</a>
</body>

