<html>
<head>
<title>AGCI EarthPulse Notes</title>
</head>
<body>
<p align=center><img src=gifs/epnotes4.gif>
<h2>EarthPulse Notes - Searchable Summaries of Current Global Change Research
</h2>
EarthPulse Notes is an accessible database of article summaries on global
change topics. Unlike typical abstracts, these summaries are written in
language that can usually be understood by educated laypeople.  While we
make an attempt to simplify complex topics, occasionally the summaries may
be semi-technical, as the subject matter dictates.  Aspen Global Change
Institute (AGCI) staff review Science, Nature, Scientific American, New
Scientist, Eos, and occasionally other publications, looking for articles
relevant to global change.<p>

When an article is selected for entry into the EarthPulse Notes database,
we identify the: Title, Author, Periodical, Date, and Page #.  
We assign keywords and write summaries which attempt to communicate the
essence of the articles, as well as put them in context, when necessary.
These notes are based on the information contained in the particular
article, not on our opinions or the state of the science.  
We seek input on how to
improve EarthPulse Notes and make it more useful.  Send your 
comments, corrections, etc. to AGCI Research Associate Susan Joy Hassol at
<a href="mailto:shassol@agci.org">shassol@agci.org</a>.<hr>
Search the <a href=http://www.ciesin.org/harvest/brokers/agci/index.html>EarthPulse Notes summaries</a> or <a href=http://www.ciesin.org/harvest/brokers/aspen/index.html>all AGCI Documents</a>.

</body>
</html> 

