<h2>Bibliographic Databases</h2>

Bibliographic database systems allow you to search or browse text-
based information such as article titles and abstracts.  These 
databases may contain information about reports and internal 
documents that are not otherwise readily available.  To use the 
commercial databases such as Dialog you need to have an account 
with that company.
<p>
<b>Non-commercial databases</b>
<dl>
<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a 
href=http://www.ns.doe.ca/>
	Canada's Environmental Knowledge Network (EKN)</a> 
<dl><dt><img align=top src=/gifs/greenball.gif>
	<a href=http://www.ns.doe.ca/cgi-bin/wais.pl>Search </a> the 
	Environment Canada Database</dl><p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a 
href=http://www.dtic.dla.mil/>
	Defense Technical Information Center</a>
	<dd>Access to and transfer of scientific and technical 
	information for DoD personnel, DoD contractors and potential 
	contractors, and other U.S. Government agency personnel and their 
	contractors.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.doe.gov/html/eren/eren.html>
        Energy Science and Technology Database (EDB)</a>
	<dd>From the Department of Energy's Office of Science and 
	Technical Information (OSTI).<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a 
href=http://www.sti.nasa.gov>
	NASA's Scientific and Technical Information Office</a> 
	<dd>Access to the NASA RECON Database, NASA Thesaurus, and 
	Selected Current Aerospace Notices.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif><a href=http://syssrv9.nrel.gov/business/international/rsvp/library_files/library.html>
	National Renewable Energy Laboratory Publications 
	Database</a> 
	<dd>References to documents written or edited by staff and 
	subcontractors of the National Renewable Energy Laboratory.<p>
</dl><p>

<b>Commercial database systems</b><p>
<dl>
<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.biosis.org>
	BIOSIS</a>
	<dd>Index that provides citations and abstracts to international 
	biological and medical literature, including <strong>Biological 
	Abstracts</strong>.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.csa.com/csa-home.html>
	Cambridge Scientific Abstracts</a>
	<dd>Databases include environmental and aquatic sciences.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://carl.org/carl.html>
	CARL Uncover</a>
	<dd>  Carl Co. provides this periodical index of more than 
	17,000 journals that allows free searching with fee-based table of 
	contents and document delivery services.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://info.cas.org/welcome.html>
	Chemical Abstracts Service (CAS)</a>
	<dd>Scientific and related information.  CAS also produces a 
	collection of chemical databases, CD-ROM products, software 
	packages, and a variety of current awareness services.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.dialog.com>
	Dialog Service</a>
	<dd>Access to 450 multidisciplinary databases from scientific 
	and technical literature that includes Aquatic Sciences and Fisheries 
	Abstracts (ASFA), GEOREF, GEOBASE, and Environmental 
	Bibliography.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.ebsco.com/>
	EBSCO Information Services</a>
	<dd>Provides a Current Citations database and document 
	delivery from more than 30,000 titles through EBSCOdoc.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.lexis.com>
	Lexis/Nexis</a>
	<dd>Access to legal, news and business information from more 
	than 5000 databases.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.oclc.org/oclc/menu/home1.htm>
	OCLC FirstSearch</a>
	<dd>Access to nearly 50 databases from OCLC, including 
	WorldCat, OCLC's Online Union Catalog; ArticleFirst and ContentsFirst 
	as well as familiar commercial databases such as ERIC, Readers Guide, 
	Periodical Abstracts, and MEDLINE.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.questel.orbit.com/patents/patres.html>
	Orbit/Questel</a>
	<dd>Patent, trademark, chemical, scientific, technical, business 
	and general news.  Also includes air environment, environmental 
	health, land environment, resource management, water environment 
	and environmental resources technology.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.sirsi.com/>
	SIRSI WebCat Demo</a>
	<dd>An "interactive, online, public access catalog" offers virtual 
	access to a million volume library collection.  Even though you cannot 
	check out any items here, it is a valuable reference resource that 
	provides indexing, identification and verification of materials.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.fiz-karlsruhe.de/stn.html>
	STN International</a>
	<dd>Access to over 190 scientific, technical, business, and 
	patent databases to users worldwide.<p>

<dt><img align=top src=/gifs/ball.yellow.gif>
<a href=http://www.umi.com/>
	UMI Information Store</a>
	<dd>Document delivery offers a variety of document types and 
	includes doctoral dissertations.<p>
</dl><p>

